text: George Percy (1580-1627) was a high-born Englishman who was a colonist in Jamestown, Virginia. Other uses of the name are: *George Percy, Earl Percy (b.1984), heir apparent to the Dukedom of Northumberland *George Percy, 5th Duke of Northumberland (1778–1867), British Tory politician known as The Earl of Beverley *George W. Percy (1847-1900), American architect in San Francisco
title: George Percy (disambiguation)
